rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"9cd1fa21b54797bd9b74a5f6b3627308d4082535a627968e86c4ae2ca96fedca","event_uuid":"e59a0b28-a511-474f-a086-22a56b21389f","position":{"commit_sha":"8f4e5fe069ae6521129136a45c2e7d18cd513194","position":"1784843690630154001-e59a0b28-a511-474f-a086-22a56b21389f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-218_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"cbe2d483-8609-4f4e-ba56-db538f86808d","comments":[],"created_at":1784783497354794001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nTicket 4af8 injected the vendor mapper entrypoints, but four core modules still reach the\nJira adapter for *scalar* concerns: `applier.py:603-605` (imports `adapters.jira.acli_subprocess`\nand calls `resolve_jira_settings(project_default=\"DIG\").project` for the cross-project safety\nguard), `fetcher.py:379-381` and `fetcher.py:441-443` (`resolve_jira_settings().project`,\nun-defaulted, for JQL scoping and parent enrichment), `_attestation.py:65-79`\n(`resolve_jira_settings(project_default=\"DIG\")` + the JIRA_URL/JIRA_USER/JIRA_API_TOKEN\nfail-fast), and `apply_handlers.py:39` (`from …adapters.jira.acli_subprocess import\nAssigneeNotFoundError`). Epic bbf1 AC3 requires zero `adapters.jira` imports in core.\n\nAn earlier version of this ticket also moved the vendor-shaped field-diff helpers\n(`diff_fields`/`extract_field`/`assignee_matches`/`local_type_to_remote`) onto the Backend\nport; plan review blocked that (correctly) because those helpers are parameterized on Jira\nsnapshot dicts, violating ADR 0035 §(d) (\"core owns diff/apply; the port only translates\").\nThat concern is now owned by the sibling canonical-shape differ stories under epic bbf1 —\nthis ticket is re-scoped to the scalar, translation-only port surface that the block never\napplied to.\n\n## Approach\n\nExtend the `Backend` Protocol in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py` with\nscalar, read-only members — none parameterized on vendor shapes:\n\n- `project` — the project/scope key with the applier's default semantics (Jira:\n  `resolve_jira_settings(project_default=\"DIG\").project`), consumed by the `applier.py:601`\n  cross-project guard.\n- `query_project` — the un-defaulted variant (Jira: `resolve_jira_settings().project`),\n  preserving the fetcher's fail-closed behavior when unset, consumed at `fetcher.py:379-381`\n  and `fetcher.py:441-443`.\n- `assert_env_ready()` — raises a new neutral `BackendEnvError(RuntimeError)` (also defined in\n  `_backend.py`) listing the missing connection essentials; JiraBackend carries the current\n  `_attestation.py:72-79` JIRA_URL/JIRA_USER/JIRA_API_TOKEN check.\n- A neutral `BackendAssigneeNotFoundError` exception defined in `_backend.py`;\n  `adapters/jira/acli_subprocess.py`'s `AssigneeNotFoundError` subclasses it, and\n  `apply_handlers.py` catches the neutral base (soft-fail semantics unchanged).\n\nAll three accessors sit on the `Backend` facade Protocol itself (not a new capability\nsub-protocol): every backend has *some* scoping/readiness story, and a project-less backend\n(e.g. a flat-list GitHub backend) returns its configured scope key (repo slug) or raises\n`BackendEnvError` from `assert_env_ready()` — the fail-closed semantics the consumers already\nhave. Update the S2 contract suite and the test-only `FakeBackend` in the same change so\nevery in-tree Backend implementor satisfies the widened Protocol (structural typing breaks\nloudly at typecheck otherwise — that IS the expand step; there are no out-of-tree\nimplementors yet, per ADR 0035).\n\nRoute the four modules through the backend instance already in scope where one exists,\notherwise through the registry seam (`select_backend(load_config())` — the exact pattern\nalready proven at `outbound_differ.py:450-454`), and delete their\n`adapters.jira`/`acli_subprocess` imports. Extend\n`tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py` with a NEW full-tree AST walker:\nthe existing `_module_level_imported_names` helper walks only `tree.body` (top-level nodes),\nbut all four vendor-import sites being removed are function-nested lazy imports\n(`fetcher.py:379`, `fetcher.py:441`, `applier.py:603`, `_attestation.py:65`) — so the new\ncase uses `ast.walk` over the whole tree, collecting every `ast.Import`/`ast.ImportFrom` at\nany nesting depth, and asserts none resolves under `adapters.jira`/`acli_subprocess` for the\nfour modules. (`inbound_probe.py:65-67` uses the same `resolve_jira_settings()` pattern but\nis deliberately NOT in this ticket's scope: it is owned whole — REST mechanics and all — by\nsibling story `aff0-b0d9-e11c-4b6a` under the same epic, which relocates it behind a\n`SupportsAbsenceProbe` capability; splitting the file between two tickets would create an\nedit-set overlap.)\n\nADR 0035 §(d)'s pinned-interface table gains a row documenting the new scalar members and\n`BackendEnvError`/`BackendAssigneeNotFoundError`, so future backend implementors have a\ncanonical reference for what the port now mandates.\n\nRejected alternative: extending the port with the vendor-shaped diff helpers — blocked by\nplan review as an ADR 0035 §(d) violation (a GitHub backend would have to implement\n`extract_field(jira_fields, …)`); the differ is made neutral by the canonical-shape sibling\nstories instead. Salvage note: Gerrit change 920 (worktree `impl-4af8-differ-di`) implemented\na superset of this ticket and passed LLM-Review +1 / Verified +1; cherry-pick only the scalar\nsubset from it, dropping the port field helpers.\n\n## Scope\n\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py (port: project/query_project/assert_env_ready + BackendAssigneeNotFoundError)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py (JiraBackend implements the new members)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/acli_subprocess.py (AssigneeNotFoundError subclasses the neutral base)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/fetcher.py, applier.py, apply_handlers.py, _attestation.py (rewire; drop vendor imports)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py (full-tree AST gate for the four modules)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/ (S2 contract suite + FakeBackend updated to the widened Protocol)\n- docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md (§(d) interface table: new scalar members + neutral exceptions)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy path: `JiraBackend.project` returns the DIG-defaulted project; `query_project` returns\n  the configured project; `assert_env_ready()` passes with all three JIRA_* set.\n- Failure/edge: `query_project` preserves today's un-defaulted fail-closed behavior when the\n  project is unset; `assert_env_ready()` raises naming exactly the missing JIRA_* vars;\n  `apply_handlers` catches `BackendAssigneeNotFoundError` when the Jira subclass is raised\n  (assignee soft-fail preserved).\n- Gate: the new AST neutrality case fails if any of the four modules re-grows an\n  `adapters.jira` import (module-level or nested).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `fetcher.py`, `applier.py`, `apply_handlers.py`, `_attestation.py` contain NO\n      `adapters.jira`/`acli_subprocess` import at ANY nesting depth — verified by the new\n      full-tree `ast.walk` case (not the top-level-only `_module_level_imported_names`\n      helper) in `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py`.\n- [ ] The Backend port exposes `project`, `query_project`, `assert_env_ready()` (raising\n      `BackendEnvError`), and `BackendAssigneeNotFoundError`; `JiraBackend` implements them\n      by delegating to `resolve_jira_settings`; the S2 contract suite and `FakeBackend` are\n      updated to the widened Protocol; behavior is identical (DIG default in the applier\n      guard, fail-closed fetcher JQL scoping, `_attestation` JIRA_* fail-fast, assignee\n      soft-fail) — verified by the unit tests named in Testing.\n- [ ] ADR 0035 §(d)'s interface table documents the new scalar members and both neutral\n      exceptions — verified by the amended ADR text in the change.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; whole test tree collects with 0 errors.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py","reason":"port: project/query_project/assert_env_ready + BackendEnvError + BackendAssigneeNotFoundError"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py","reason":"JiraBackend implements the scalar members"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/acli_subprocess.py","reason":"AssigneeNotFoundError subclasses the neutral base"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/fetcher.py","reason":"backend.query_project; drop acli_subprocess import"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/applier.py","reason":"backend.project; drop acli_subprocess import"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_handlers.py","reason":"catch neutral BackendAssigneeNotFoundError"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_attestation.py","reason":"assert_env_ready via backend; drop acli_subprocess import"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py","reason":"full-tree ast.walk gate for the four modules"},{"path":"docs/adr/0035-reconciler-vendor-adapter-seam.md","reason":"§(d) interface table: scalar members + neutral exceptions"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"82e8c644-d539-477f-91fd-cfffe3fc8b3b","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"97f2-2d98-2eff-41c1","ticket_type":"task","title":"Backend port scalar surface: project scope, env-readiness fail-fast, neutral assignee error (fetcher/applier/apply_handlers/_attestation)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["e2ad3f5b-c074-4339-8533-364221603061","590dc702-4072-4a2e-b07b-bd7b4dff89d0","2ef440e6-594c-45e0-8f37-c3ca64e7342f","b4ba7c72-10ae-4fb9-a238-8772fa6c0c69","439cd048-294f-4e22-a1e2-384265e79b95","7f250a52-3f89-44b2-80d6-5c0a03510724","dc6417b2-e9e5-4f04-b204-d91b306eb836","82e8c644-d539-477f-91fd-cfffe3fc8b3b","22ce9dcc-52bd-4843-903c-762c06aa3d94","1e55588f-8e50-4152-9b8a-b5c46485566c","e59a0b28-a511-474f-a086-22a56b21389f"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784843690630154002,"uuid":"9e4b605d-95f3-4cf2-8562-69792d0d71e1"}